00:54.387 --> 00:55.688
Hi.

00:55.689 --> 00:59.692
I'm Sam Turner and we're here at VICE
Headquarters in Williamsburg, Brooklyn

00:59.693 --> 01:01.694
with one of our favorite
fashion photographers,

01:01.695 --> 01:04.697
Just a few nights ago, we
were all hanging out together

01:04.697 --> 01:08.768
when he let slip a comment about his
sister that had us practically speechless

01:08.769 --> 01:10.270
for the better part of an hour.

01:10.271 --> 01:15.040
After hearing the full story, we immediately
thought, we have got to do a piece on it.

01:38.965 --> 01:40.233
Should I read it?

01:40.234 --> 01:41.468
Read it.

01:41.469 --> 01:45.205
Okay, it says, "Dear Patrick, sorry you
have not heard from me in so long.

01:45.206 --> 01:47.974
I have been working hard with
everyone to build a community

01:47.975 --> 01:50.243
where we can finally live
free as God intended.

01:50.244 --> 01:52.445
We're not there yet,
but we're so close.

01:52.446 --> 01:55.982
It's the most beautiful place I have ever
been and I would love if you came to visit.

01:55.983 --> 01:58.517
We have so much love here
but I miss your face."

01:59.319 --> 02:01.800
Then it says "Love, Caroline,"
and there's a phone number.

02:30.650 --> 02:32.352
We've been to some
of the most chaotic,

02:32.353 --> 02:34.754
fucked up, war-torn
places in the world,

02:34.755 --> 02:39.659
but never somewhere for something
as personal and bizarre as this.

02:39.660 --> 02:42.028
So here we are, about
to leave New York City,

02:42.029 --> 02:45.632
to set out to find your sister
in a remote part of the world,

02:45.633 --> 02:48.935
to see what this community she is
living in is really all about.

02:48.936 --> 02:50.503
Maybe we can call this one

02:50.504 --> 02:53.271
the "VICE guide to the
Carter family reunion".

03:39.185 --> 03:43.723
<i>♪ One night to be confused
one night to speed up truth ♪</i>

03:43.724 --> 03:46.993
<i>♪ We had a promise made ♪</i>

03:46.994 --> 03:49.696
<i>♪ Four hands and then away ♪</i>

03:49.697 --> 03:52.432
<i>♪ Both under influence ♪</i>

03:52.433 --> 03:55.201
<i>♪ We had divine scent ♪</i>

03:55.202 --> 03:57.503
<i>♪ To know what to say ♪</i>

03:57.504 --> 04:00.340
<i>♪ Mind is a razor blade ♪</i>

04:00.341 --> 04:04.077
<i>♪ To call for hands of above ♪</i>

04:04.078 --> 04:06.212
<i>♪ To lean on ♪</i>

04:06.213 --> 04:11.850
<i>♪ Wouldn't be good
enough for me, no ♪</i>

04:33.139 --> 04:36.876
<i>♪ To call for hands of above ♪</i>

04:36.877 --> 04:38.778
<i>♪ To lean on ♪</i>

04:38.779 --> 04:44.816
<i>♪ Wouldn't be good
enough for me, no ♪</i>

05:07.307 --> 05:10.677
I'll be back tomorrow at 8:00 a.m.

05:10.678 --> 05:13.513
I'll wait for one hour
and then I will leave.

05:13.514 --> 05:14.947
With or without you.

05:14.948 --> 05:16.516
Don't worry, we'll be here.

05:16.517 --> 05:19.084
I'm not worried.
8:00 a.m.

05:31.798 --> 05:32.832
Who is Patrick?

05:32.833 --> 05:34.599
Yeah.
That's me.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.103
We were not told you'd
be bringing others.

05:39.472 --> 05:40.840
There are three total.

05:40.841 --> 05:42.542
Is there a problem?
We're all together.

05:42.543 --> 05:44.610
We have to get clearance to
bring them to the Parish.

05:44.611 --> 05:46.444
Please, stop filming me, sir.

05:49.982 --> 05:51.984
They came with me.
I can't just leave them here.

05:51.985 --> 05:54.320
My sister invited us.

05:54.321 --> 05:56.689
My sister's name is
Caroline Carter.

05:56.690 --> 05:57.990
Hold on.

05:57.991 --> 05:59.058
I don't understand
if there's problem.

05:59.059 --> 06:00.326
Hold on.

06:00.327 --> 06:01.893
It should be all arranged.

06:04.731 --> 06:06.332
<i>Okay.</i>
<i>Bring them in.</i>

06:06.333 --> 06:07.500
Copy that.

06:07.501 --> 06:09.267
It's okay.

06:10.570 --> 06:11.637
Come with me.

06:11.638 --> 06:13.271
Let's go.

06:15.241 --> 06:17.243
It's okay.

06:17.244 --> 06:19.145
Get in the back.

06:19.146 --> 06:20.646
The truck?

06:20.647 --> 06:22.147
Get in the back.

06:44.904 --> 06:46.538
So far so good.

07:09.562 --> 07:11.631
Well, here we are,
we made it, kind of.

07:11.632 --> 07:13.199
We don't have a local
fixer on this one,

07:13.200 --> 07:14.267
and the first thing that happens is

07:14.268 --> 07:16.702
Patrick almost getting into an
argument with one of our guides.

07:16.703 --> 07:18.204
You know those are the
guys you want on your side

07:18.205 --> 07:20.072
when you are out in
places like this.

07:20.073 --> 07:23.309
Maybe New York has made me soft,
but these are the moments,

07:23.310 --> 07:25.578
every time we make one of
these things, where I realize

07:25.579 --> 07:26.979
it might have been
the worst idea ever.

07:26.980 --> 07:29.681
No, we've definitely
had worse ideas.

07:31.784 --> 07:32.952
I don't know why you're laughing.

07:32.953 --> 07:34.053
Get a shot of his shoes.

07:34.054 --> 07:37.824
Where did you think you were
going, wearing shoes like those?

07:37.825 --> 07:39.659
I thought you traveled
for work all the time?

07:39.660 --> 07:41.928
Yeah, to LA, and fucking Paris.

07:41.929 --> 07:43.095
Closest I come to this shit

07:43.096 --> 07:45.164
is shooting some model
in a field in Jersey.

07:45.165 --> 07:47.866
Dude, you're in fashion,
you should own some boots.

08:12.458 --> 08:13.892
Turn the camera off!

08:17.196 --> 08:18.865
Turn it off!

08:18.866 --> 08:20.732
Turn it off!

08:29.775 --> 08:33.145
So things have not improved.

08:33.145 --> 08:37.350
We didn't get shot, but
we have to be careful

08:37.351 --> 08:39.784
not to let them catch us filming.

08:39.785 --> 08:43.523
Patrick is over there explaining
who we are, what we're doing.

08:43.524 --> 08:47.659
I'm not sure if that will
make things better or worse.

08:48.494 --> 08:51.930
We're hoping that he can find his
sister and straighten all this out.

08:53.032 --> 08:56.302
And if Patrick starts to get shot
at, I'm going the fuck that way.

08:56.303 --> 08:58.169
As quickly as possible.

08:59.138 --> 09:01.807
They want our passports,

09:01.808 --> 09:05.011
but I'm not giving up
my passport to anybody.

09:05.012 --> 09:08.748
Also, there is some
talk of a donation.

09:08.749 --> 09:12.151
Not sure how sizeable
that donation has to be.

09:12.152 --> 09:16.321
So far this is nothing at all like the
hippie commune we were expecting.

09:17.557 --> 09:18.658
Patrick?

09:18.659 --> 09:19.926
Okay.
See, there she is.

09:19.927 --> 09:22.026
Hey, it's okay guys.
It's okay.

09:23.029 --> 09:27.432
Caroline, did you tell them?
All right, come on guys.

09:31.938 --> 09:33.072
Oh, I'm so glad you're here.

09:33.073 --> 09:35.441
I'm so glad to see you.
What's with all this?

09:35.442 --> 09:38.177
Oh, I'll explain it inside.

09:38.178 --> 09:39.211
- Hi.
- Hi.

09:39.212 --> 09:41.213
I'm Caroline.
Nice to meet you.

09:41.214 --> 09:43.282
You too.
I'm Sam, this is Jake.

09:43.283 --> 09:45.418
Hi.

09:45.419 --> 09:47.587
We didn't know you were coming.
I'm so sorry.

09:47.588 --> 09:49.088
It's just... We're really
happy to have you.

09:49.089 --> 09:51.357
There's someone cleaning out
a cabin right now for you both.

09:51.358 --> 09:52.425
Great.

09:52.426 --> 09:54.961
Is it all right if I keep filming?

09:54.962 --> 09:56.696
Yeah.
Yeah, of course, of course.

09:56.697 --> 10:01.467
I would just hope that you would
leave this last experience out.

10:01.468 --> 10:04.370
It in no way reflects what
you are about to see.

10:04.371 --> 10:07.373
The guns are just a precautionary
measure because of where we are.

10:07.374 --> 10:09.742
Down here everything needs
some level of security.

10:09.743 --> 10:10.743
Sure, we understand.

10:10.744 --> 10:11.744
You want to go inside?

10:11.745 --> 10:12.745
Yeah. Yeah.

10:12.746 --> 10:13.746
Yeah? Okay, cool.

10:13.747 --> 10:15.213
Thanks, guys.

10:21.587 --> 10:23.990
My God, I can't believe I'm
looking at you right now.

10:23.991 --> 10:25.758
Your hair is so short.

10:25.759 --> 10:27.326
Yeah, I cut it.

10:27.327 --> 10:28.761
You look good.
You look healthy.

10:28.762 --> 10:30.096
Thank you.

10:30.097 --> 10:31.497
I can't believe this is
where you are living.

10:31.498 --> 10:33.766
Oh, just wait until you see it all.

10:33.767 --> 10:36.636
Here we are.
Welcome to Eden Parish.

10:36.637 --> 10:38.004
What do you think?

10:38.005 --> 10:39.338
It's great, right?

10:39.339 --> 10:45.344
<i>Children, we have some special
visitors to the parish today.</i>

10:45.345 --> 10:47.480
<i>Let's show them our hospitality</i>

10:47.481 --> 10:50.616
<i>and represent ourselves in the
ways the Lord has taught us.</i>

10:50.617 --> 10:52.985
<i>- God bless you all.</i>
- Oh, yeah.

10:52.986 --> 10:56.922
I don't think that we slept more
than three hours in a night

10:56.923 --> 10:59.291
for six months when
we were building it.

10:59.292 --> 11:02.795
But Father had a vision, and
he was of course right.

11:02.796 --> 11:06.431
And we built Heaven here on Earth.

11:07.433 --> 11:09.035
Who is Father?

11:09.036 --> 11:10.770
Oh, right.
Yeah.

11:10.771 --> 11:13.506
Probably sounds weird
to you guys, huh?

11:13.507 --> 11:16.642
Well, he's the guy that
started all of this.

11:16.643 --> 11:18.177
He's the reason that
I'm still alive.

11:18.178 --> 11:20.680
He's the reason that
all of us are here.

11:20.681 --> 11:23.149
He's a genius, I swear.

11:23.150 --> 11:27.453
I know it sounds strange, but we all call
him that because it's just easier for us.

11:27.454 --> 11:28.954
Is that him on the loud speaker?

11:28.955 --> 11:30.556
Uh-huh.

11:30.557 --> 11:32.058
Can we speak with
him at some point?

11:32.059 --> 11:33.893
Um.

11:33.894 --> 11:37.663
I know you guys are Patrick's
friends and everything,

11:37.664 --> 11:40.199
but we've got to be really
careful about media exposure.

11:40.200 --> 11:43.536
None of this would be possible
without some level of secrecy.

11:43.537 --> 11:45.471
Secrecy, from whom?

11:45.472 --> 11:46.572
People like us?

11:46.573 --> 11:48.708
Or you mean like the
local government?

11:48.709 --> 11:51.310
A little of both.

11:51.311 --> 11:54.480
There are some people out there
that want to stop what we're doing.

11:54.481 --> 11:57.316
They think it's wrong, but
I personally have no idea

11:57.317 --> 11:59.819
why anyone would think
that this was wrong.

11:59.820 --> 12:01.854
I've never been so happy
in my entire life,

12:01.855 --> 12:04.824
and we grew up wealthy
on the upper west side.

12:04.825 --> 12:08.360
But that's not living, at least not to me.
This is living.

12:08.361 --> 12:10.596
We all built this
together as a community.

12:10.597 --> 12:12.964
We would do anything
to keep it safe.

12:17.103 --> 12:20.506
So some of our residents
agreed to move out of here

12:20.507 --> 12:24.076
so that you guys could
stay here with us tonight,

12:24.077 --> 12:27.079
but Patrick is going to stay
with me in the main house.

12:27.080 --> 12:29.381
And I know it doesn't
seem like much,

12:29.382 --> 12:31.751
but you guys should be pretty
comfortable for the night.

12:31.752 --> 12:33.385
When we first got here, some
of our residents said that

12:33.386 --> 12:35.721
they had the best
sleep of their lives.

12:35.722 --> 12:38.023
It's so peaceful and just
wait until you see the stars.

12:38.024 --> 12:40.392
They're so beautiful.
It's great, thank you.

12:40.393 --> 12:42.962
Should we come find you
once we get settled?

12:42.963 --> 12:45.898
We would actually like to talk to you
at some point if you're cool with that.

12:45.899 --> 12:49.401
Just... but take your time
because I would really

12:49.402 --> 12:51.237
love to spend some
time with my brother.

12:51.238 --> 12:53.671
Take him, we can't give him away.

12:54.406 --> 12:57.143
But really, if you guys need
anything at all, anything,

12:57.144 --> 13:00.546
the main house is just across the
field, just behind that pavilion.

13:00.547 --> 13:01.747
- Do you see it?
- Yeah.

13:01.748 --> 13:04.383
Feel free to just wander around and
get acquainted with the place.

13:04.384 --> 13:06.252
Our residents are
really nice people.

13:06.253 --> 13:07.386
Sounds good.

13:07.387 --> 13:08.554
Mm-hmm.

13:08.555 --> 13:10.156
- You ready?
- Yeah.

13:10.157 --> 13:11.157
Well, welcome.

13:11.158 --> 13:12.925
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

13:12.926 --> 13:15.795
Okay, I guess I'm going
to go with her for a bit.

13:15.796 --> 13:17.819
All right.
See you in a few.

13:17.820 --> 13:19.589
Later.
See you, man.

13:28.073 --> 13:30.041
You want the top or bottom?

13:37.183 --> 13:39.084
She's selling this
place pretty hard.

13:39.085 --> 13:40.953
Right?

13:40.954 --> 13:42.788
Best night's sleep of your life...

13:42.789 --> 13:44.288
Yeah.

13:48.694 --> 13:50.196
How freaked out were
you back on the truck?

13:50.197 --> 13:51.696
Dude.

13:52.464 --> 13:54.232
Why did they have machine guns?

13:56.602 --> 13:58.604
I'm gonna switch cards so
if anything gets weird,

13:58.605 --> 14:00.339
we at least have the
footage we shot so far.

14:00.340 --> 14:02.106
Good call.

14:19.058 --> 14:21.994
<i>Peace I give you, children.</i>

14:21.995 --> 14:24.129
<i>Do not let your hearts be troubled.</i>

14:24.130 --> 14:25.831
<i>Do not be afraid.</i>

14:25.832 --> 14:29.134
<i>It's another day for us in paradise.</i>

14:29.135 --> 14:30.135
Hi.

14:30.136 --> 14:34.340
<i>When brothers and
sisters live in unity.</i>

14:34.341 --> 14:35.574
<i>God bless you all.</i>

14:35.575 --> 14:37.141
Hi.

14:39.745 --> 14:43.414
I do not know who
to approach first.

14:44.250 --> 14:45.517
They'll come to me.

14:45.518 --> 14:47.251
Hey, how you doing?

14:48.587 --> 14:51.022
Not that one, I guess.

14:58.497 --> 15:00.298
Oh, got her.
Got her.

15:05.671 --> 15:07.172
Hi.

15:07.173 --> 15:08.507
Hi.

15:08.508 --> 15:09.508
How are you?

15:09.509 --> 15:10.676
I'm fine.
How about yourself?

15:10.677 --> 15:11.677
I'm very well.

15:11.678 --> 15:13.879
My name is Lorraine Davis,

15:13.880 --> 15:16.749
but everyone around here
just calls me Miss D.

15:16.750 --> 15:18.918
So how did you get
involved with this place?

15:18.919 --> 15:20.185
Through the church.

15:20.186 --> 15:23.789
Now Father had came into
the area where we lived

15:23.790 --> 15:28.560
and I had seen signs
plastered all around town.

15:28.561 --> 15:34.033
Signs inviting people to come out
and to help better themselves

15:34.034 --> 15:37.703
and to get a better
relationship with God.

15:37.704 --> 15:41.440
So I went down there to the church

15:41.441 --> 15:45.311
and before that sermon
was over, I was sold.

15:45.312 --> 15:48.714
That man has a way of speaking,

15:48.715 --> 15:54.053
a way of making you just feel better,
and I'd never felt that way before.

15:54.054 --> 15:58.090
And it wasn't long
after that he chose me

15:58.091 --> 16:00.326
to be one of the lucky ones

16:00.327 --> 16:03.462
to come down here and be
a part of all of this.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.597
Oh, were you reluctant
to leave your home?

16:05.598 --> 16:06.966
Oh, no.

16:06.967 --> 16:08.600
After my husband had passed,

16:08.601 --> 16:13.237
there just wasn't
anything here for me.

16:14.473 --> 16:19.445
My faith is what was
most important.

16:19.446 --> 16:23.381
This is right where I belong.

16:25.451 --> 16:27.586
We're with VICE.

16:27.587 --> 16:30.255
We want to talk with someone around our
age about what it's like living here.

16:30.256 --> 16:31.256
I know VICE.

16:31.257 --> 16:33.492
Cool.
Are you from Australia?

16:33.493 --> 16:34.860
Melbourne, yeah.

16:34.861 --> 16:36.862
How did you end up here?

16:36.863 --> 16:39.965
I mean, what were you doing
before you came to this place?

16:39.966 --> 16:41.867
I was an artist living in Brooklyn.

16:41.868 --> 16:43.102
What kind of art do you do?

16:43.103 --> 16:44.370
All kinds.

16:44.371 --> 16:46.839
Painting, poetry, performance.

16:46.840 --> 16:50.009
Do you ever miss the technology
you were accustomed to?

16:50.010 --> 16:52.378
Even just communicating easier

16:52.379 --> 16:54.380
or knowing what's going on
with the outside world?

16:54.381 --> 16:56.382
You must, a little bit?

16:56.383 --> 16:58.617
I don't need the
internet to communicate.

16:58.618 --> 17:01.153
People lived without it
for thousands of years.

17:01.154 --> 17:03.856
It's just another
unhealthy addiction.

17:03.857 --> 17:06.791
Here we talk to each other in
person, not through satellites.

17:06.792 --> 17:10.128
What about your
family in Australia?

17:10.130 --> 17:11.561
Do they know where you are?

17:12.397 --> 17:15.000
This is my family now.

17:15.001 --> 17:17.301
Father has given me more
than I ever dreamed of.

17:17.303 --> 17:19.538
I'm so grateful for that.

17:19.539 --> 17:21.173
Okay.

17:21.174 --> 17:23.308
Fair enough.

17:23.309 --> 17:24.909
Thanks.

17:32.918 --> 17:34.053
Oh, hi.

17:34.054 --> 17:35.687
Hi.
Can we come in?

17:35.688 --> 17:37.890
Sure.

17:37.891 --> 17:39.825
What is this place?

17:39.826 --> 17:44.830
This is our medical center and
temporarily our day-care.

17:44.831 --> 17:51.203
I help with any conditions our residents
may have, especially our seniors.

17:51.204 --> 17:54.339
And Miss Phoebe in there helps
takes care of some of the children

17:54.340 --> 17:56.442
while their parents
are in the fields.

17:56.443 --> 17:58.444
Are there a lot of
children and seniors here?

17:58.445 --> 18:00.045
Oh, yes.

18:00.046 --> 18:04.083
We have over 35 boys and
girls under the age of 10,

18:04.084 --> 18:08.053
and at least 60 or so seniors.

18:08.054 --> 18:11.489
That's how our parish really got
its start, helping those seniors.

18:12.291 --> 18:14.593
Has anyone actually been born here?

18:14.594 --> 18:17.729
Oh, we've birthed
seven babies to date.

18:17.730 --> 18:20.464
Seven?
All here?

18:21.233 --> 18:23.067
That's right.
Right here.

18:24.870 --> 18:27.372
Why are you so surprised?

18:27.373 --> 18:31.977
People are born around the world every
day in conditions worse than this.

18:31.978 --> 18:35.447
It's not the hospital that has
the baby, it's the mother.

18:35.448 --> 18:37.882
He's just nervous because
his wife's pregnant.

18:39.118 --> 18:41.220
Really?
When is she due?

18:41.221 --> 18:42.387
Next month.

18:42.388 --> 18:43.388
Is this your first?

18:43.389 --> 18:44.389
Yeah.

18:44.390 --> 18:46.492
The first are the most exciting.

18:46.493 --> 18:47.626
Congratulations.

18:47.627 --> 18:50.262
Thank you.

18:50.263 --> 18:52.464
Where do all these
supplies come from?

18:52.465 --> 18:53.465
Do you get them locally?

18:53.466 --> 18:55.601
Well, we brought a lot with us,

18:55.602 --> 18:59.004
but thank heavens we haven't needed
to use much of the medication.

18:59.005 --> 19:03.475
But we are prepared for
all types of emergencies.

19:03.476 --> 19:05.777
Who pays for it all?

19:05.778 --> 19:07.746
We did.

19:07.747 --> 19:11.150
Well, in so many words, anyway.

19:11.151 --> 19:16.755
When many of us first came to the
parish, we sold everything we had.

19:16.756 --> 19:20.492
When several hundred people come
together, you would be surprised

19:20.493 --> 19:22.861
that how much you can
get accomplished.

19:22.862 --> 19:25.531
Everyone just gave up what
they had to come here?

19:25.532 --> 19:27.166
That's right.

19:27.167 --> 19:30.369
We sold our homes and we donated
the profits to the church.

19:30.370 --> 19:32.703
And we would do it again.

19:33.872 --> 19:39.311
Father is a businessman
on top of all things.

19:39.312 --> 19:42.713
Sometimes that gets overlooked.

19:57.563 --> 19:59.965
- So where are you guys from?
- Oh, we're from the hood, man.

19:59.966 --> 20:01.033
Yeah.

20:01.034 --> 20:02.334
I'm saying we had nothing
where we was from.

20:02.335 --> 20:04.836
You know, five of us
lived in two rooms.

20:04.837 --> 20:06.171
And that's how you want to live?

20:06.172 --> 20:08.340
Me, Robert, our mother
and two sisters,

20:08.341 --> 20:10.342
we all came down here together.

20:10.343 --> 20:12.477
And I mean, honestly,
it's just changed us.

20:12.478 --> 20:14.179
We're from a violent community.

20:14.180 --> 20:15.581
I don't know, man.

20:15.582 --> 20:17.816
If we didn't come down here,

20:17.817 --> 20:18.917
God knows what would
have happened to us.

20:18.918 --> 20:20.419
Oh, yeah, yeah, if you had told us

20:20.420 --> 20:23.222
we'll be out there with the white
dudes and all these people...

20:23.223 --> 20:25.122
Yeah, yeah.
We'd just say you was crazy.

20:26.058 --> 20:30.495
It's like, we look at you all and
it's like you are the crazy ones.

20:30.496 --> 20:31.997
Yeah.
I mean...

20:31.998 --> 20:33.432
This is how we're
supposed to be living.

20:33.433 --> 20:35.601
You know, everybody
here is in it together.

20:35.602 --> 20:36.602
That's right.

20:36.603 --> 20:37.836
You know, there's no
one man for himself,

20:37.837 --> 20:39.371
it's like God watches over us.

20:39.372 --> 20:41.006
Yeah.

20:41.007 --> 20:42.507
- We watch over each other.
- That's right, man.

20:42.508 --> 20:45.877
Do you see yourself ever going
back to the United States?

20:45.878 --> 20:47.512
Never.
There's no point.

20:47.513 --> 20:50.215
I ain't never going back, man.

20:50.216 --> 20:51.717
I'd die before I go back.

20:51.718 --> 20:54.019
It's real.

20:54.020 --> 20:56.121
Hey, can I play some
ball with you guys?

20:56.122 --> 20:57.256
Yeah, man.

20:57.257 --> 20:58.257
Come on.

20:58.258 --> 20:59.725
Can he ball?
He can really ball.

20:59.726 --> 21:01.292
No.

21:32.157 --> 21:34.059
<i>So we talked to a bunch
of the people here</i>

21:34.060 --> 21:36.662
<i>and what we know so far
is that everyone thinks</i>

21:36.663 --> 21:39.131
<i>this is the best place
they've ever been.</i>

21:39.132 --> 21:41.066
<i>They have their own farming,
their own medical center,</i>

21:41.067 --> 21:43.435
<i>their own daycare,
their own everything.</i>

21:43.436 --> 21:45.070
<i>As far as utopias go,</i>

21:45.071 --> 21:46.905
<i>it has something for everybody.</i>

21:46.906 --> 21:49.308
If it's spirituality
you want, they got it.

21:49.309 --> 21:51.810
If it's progressive
politics, they got it.

21:51.811 --> 21:54.179
If it's a technology
free hippy lifestyle

21:54.180 --> 21:56.682
you're looking for,
they got that, too.

21:56.683 --> 21:58.950
I can't help but think desperation

21:58.951 --> 22:00.819
is a lot of what
brought people here,

22:00.820 --> 22:04.788
but if they're happy now,
who am I to say anything?

22:05.590 --> 22:07.526
We're about to head
to the main house

22:07.527 --> 22:09.194
to meet back up with
Patrick and Caroline

22:09.195 --> 22:13.332
to see if we can do an interview with
this Father everyone keeps talking about.

22:13.333 --> 22:16.601
I'm trying to keep it together, so
I can ask intelligent questions,

22:16.602 --> 22:20.971
but jet lag's kicked in and
I am starting to melt.

22:22.708 --> 22:24.543
Jake, what do you think
of all this so far?

22:24.544 --> 22:28.212
Give me your
professional assessment.

22:31.116 --> 22:32.984
Um, I don't know.

22:32.985 --> 22:36.120
I mean, I'm naturally
cynical, but...

22:39.624 --> 22:42.227
The fact that a bunch of
drug addicts and alcoholics

22:42.228 --> 22:45.329
actually pulled this thing together
is a little bit impressive.

22:46.732 --> 22:50.234
Fact that they sold all their
worldly possessions to do it.

22:51.370 --> 22:54.605
I don't know, just throws up the
red flag for me a little bit.

22:55.374 --> 23:00.078
I feel like, I mean, if this
is like a place to come

23:00.079 --> 23:03.515
and get clean or do a little
bit of thinking for a month,

23:03.516 --> 23:05.150
it's perfect.

23:05.151 --> 23:08.353
I think it is an actual
sustainable lifestyle for,

23:08.354 --> 23:12.257
you know, 60 something
elderly people.

23:12.258 --> 23:14.259
I mean, that medical
center is great,

23:14.260 --> 23:19.496
but that's not really going to cut
it, in my professional opinion.

23:26.271 --> 23:28.173
What are you gonna ask this guy?

23:28.174 --> 23:29.773
I don't know yet.

23:31.042 --> 23:32.677
Are you going in
with tough questions

23:32.678 --> 23:35.145
or you're just gonna wait
and see what the vibe is?

23:36.047 --> 23:37.916
I'm coming at him.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.284
Okay.

23:39.285 --> 23:41.553
Well, I'm gonna see
if he'll wear a wire,

23:41.554 --> 23:43.554
gonna try and mic you guys up.

23:48.126 --> 23:50.194
Sam, we got a little one.

23:54.900 --> 23:57.269
Hi.

23:57.270 --> 23:58.937
What's your name?

23:58.938 --> 24:01.807
Savannah.
There you are.

24:01.808 --> 24:03.942
Well, I've been looking
all over for you.

24:03.943 --> 24:05.577
Hi, Savannah.

24:05.578 --> 24:07.279
Don't mind her.
She is a mute.

24:07.280 --> 24:08.313
Oh.

24:08.314 --> 24:09.714
You friends of Caroline's?

24:09.715 --> 24:11.583
Yeah.
We're with VICE.

24:11.584 --> 24:13.544
We want to maybe do a
story about this place.

24:14.319 --> 24:15.654
What kind of a story?

24:15.655 --> 24:17.823
We don't really know yet.

24:17.824 --> 24:19.458
You're not gonna make
fun of us, are you?

24:19.459 --> 24:20.926
No, not at all.

24:20.927 --> 24:23.962
We were just saying how
impressive all this is.

24:23.963 --> 24:27.299
Hey, would you mind doing
a quick interview?

24:27.300 --> 24:29.334
We talked with a few people
about how they ended up here

24:29.335 --> 24:31.436
and it'd be great if we could get

24:31.437 --> 24:33.972
- a mother's perspective on that.
- No, thank you.

24:33.973 --> 24:39.444
We're not allowed to talk about the
Parish, especially to outsiders.

24:39.445 --> 24:41.111
Come on, sweetheart.

24:44.749 --> 24:46.351
Did she just call us outsiders?

24:46.352 --> 24:47.885
Yeah.

24:52.624 --> 24:54.493
It's kind of a different vibe, huh?

24:54.494 --> 24:55.893
Yeah.

25:08.640 --> 25:09.674
Hey.

25:09.675 --> 25:10.675
Hey.

25:10.676 --> 25:11.810
How are you doing?

25:11.811 --> 25:13.345
I'll see you guys later.

25:13.346 --> 25:14.779
You guys enjoying
yourselves so far?

25:14.780 --> 25:15.780
Definitely.

25:15.781 --> 25:17.516
Yeah?
So good news.

25:17.517 --> 25:20.552
I spoke with Father and he agreed
to allow you an interview.

25:20.553 --> 25:21.620
- Great.
- Yeah.

25:21.621 --> 25:23.788
He is not really feeling
very well right now.

25:23.789 --> 25:26.224
He just took some of his medication.
Oh, is he sick?

25:26.225 --> 25:27.792
No.
It's nothing serious.

25:27.793 --> 25:30.629
It's just sometimes the
medication upsets his stomach.

25:30.630 --> 25:34.299
So he agreed to sit for an interview
tonight at the gathering.

25:34.300 --> 25:36.368
We're planning an
event for your visit.

25:36.369 --> 25:40.405
It's gonna be music and dancing,
you'll love it, especially you.

25:40.406 --> 25:45.176
So we would love it if you would
look over this document I prepared.

25:45.177 --> 25:47.812
It'll give you a little bit
more information about us

25:47.813 --> 25:49.814
and it should help
with your questions.

25:49.815 --> 25:53.016
He is only gonna sit for half an
hour and then the party will begin.

25:53.818 --> 25:55.253
What time does the party start?

25:55.254 --> 25:57.055
It begins at sun down.

25:57.056 --> 25:59.925
If you just want to meet me
in front of the pavilion,

25:59.926 --> 26:01.326
and then I'll take
care of the rest.

26:01.327 --> 26:02.327
Perfect.
Thank you.

26:02.328 --> 26:03.428
Okay.
Of course.

26:03.429 --> 26:04.896
We have nothing to hide.

26:04.897 --> 26:06.031
So if you'll excuse me,

26:06.032 --> 26:08.333
I have some more planning
to do before tonight,

26:08.334 --> 26:09.534
so I'll just see you
guys in a little bit.

26:09.535 --> 26:10.535
Sounds good.

26:10.536 --> 26:11.570
Okay.

26:11.571 --> 26:13.604
- Yeah. Thanks, Caroline.
- Mm-hmm.

26:15.707 --> 26:17.075
How is it going, man?

26:17.076 --> 26:19.344
Man, I got some amazing
pictures so far, dude.

26:19.345 --> 26:21.612
I can make a whole
book out of this.

26:22.847 --> 26:25.183
Look at these faces, man.

26:25.184 --> 26:26.617
Jesus.

26:27.352 --> 26:29.721
You know, I can make something
really cool out of this

26:29.722 --> 26:31.556
and it'd be great for me, 'cause
then I could set up a show

26:31.557 --> 26:32.857
with Milt when I get back.

26:32.858 --> 26:34.324
That's right.

26:35.727 --> 26:38.629
Oh, no, that's what my ticket
on fashion looks like.

26:40.231 --> 26:41.232
What have you guys been up to?

26:41.233 --> 26:44.134
Well, we talked to a
bunch of the locals.

26:44.970 --> 26:46.471
- And?
- It's pretty wild.

26:46.472 --> 26:48.974
Yeah.

26:48.975 --> 26:50.874
Strange group of people.

26:52.744 --> 26:54.211
Nah, it's incredible.

26:54.946 --> 26:57.616
Had a few bizarre
interactions, but you know...

26:57.617 --> 27:01.620
Where I'm staying, a full extra bedroom,
office, can't even wrap my head around it.

27:01.621 --> 27:05.590
The construction aspect is pretty
impressive I have to admit.

27:05.591 --> 27:09.761
Do you think your... Do you think
your sister wants to stay?

27:09.762 --> 27:10.795
It seems like it.

27:10.796 --> 27:13.131
I thought I was gonna have
to come here and rescue her

27:13.132 --> 27:15.634
but she seems good and she's
definitely done worse.

27:15.635 --> 27:18.735
I don't know how I'm gonna describe
this to my parents, but...

27:19.638 --> 27:22.507
Um, we're rolling, so
let's do that letter.

27:22.508 --> 27:24.174
All right.

27:31.016 --> 27:32.751
"Distinguished guests..."

27:32.752 --> 27:36.021
Well, does it say
distinguished guests?

27:36.022 --> 27:38.023
Says it.

27:38.024 --> 27:40.025
"Welcome to Eden Parish.

27:40.026 --> 27:41.760
Father wants only to
create a community

27:41.761 --> 27:43.662
where peace and love are cherished,

27:43.663 --> 27:46.865
where the needs of one another are met on
equal levels as we're all God's children

27:46.866 --> 27:49.300
and it is how He Himself
intended us to live.

27:49.301 --> 27:52.037
We do not seek to isolate
ourselves from the outside world,

27:52.038 --> 27:55.807
but we do seek a distance from
imperialism, violence, poverty, racism

27:55.808 --> 27:59.010
and all other unacceptable
attacks on basic human rights.

27:59.011 --> 28:02.447
These conditions have all become
commonplace in modern societies.

28:02.448 --> 28:04.683
Father created Eden Parish
not as a place to get away,

28:04.684 --> 28:06.317
but as a place to start over.

28:06.318 --> 28:07.452
It is a new beginning.

28:07.453 --> 28:11.189
Sincerely, the loving
congregation of Eden Parish."

28:11.190 --> 28:13.825
Define imperialism.

28:13.826 --> 28:15.726
Define imperialism.

28:17.028 --> 28:18.595
Idiots.

28:23.301 --> 28:24.836
You're getting a signal?

28:24.837 --> 28:26.103
No.

28:26.838 --> 28:28.206
Okay.

28:28.207 --> 28:29.728
What are you doing on your phone?

28:31.543 --> 28:36.047
Dude, she is still gonna be pregnant
tomorrow when you get home.

28:36.048 --> 28:37.682
They might have a satellite
phone in the office.

28:37.683 --> 28:39.350
They don't have a satellite
phone in the office.

28:39.351 --> 28:42.854
You know, you don't need to
encourage this kind of behavior.

28:42.855 --> 28:44.355
Okay but I saw a room
with a lot of equipment.

28:44.356 --> 28:46.757
He is fine.
You're fine.

28:57.202 --> 28:58.603
<i>Would all Parish members</i>

28:58.604 --> 29:01.740
<i>please report to the
pavilion no later than 7:45.</i>

29:01.741 --> 29:04.843
<i>We're having a very
special meeting tonight,</i>

29:04.844 --> 29:06.745
<i>for Father and our visitors.</i>

29:06.746 --> 29:08.513
<i>Everyone is required to attend.</i>

29:08.514 --> 29:10.380
<i>God bless.</i>

29:21.259 --> 29:23.728
So we're gonna have you
guys set up over here

29:23.729 --> 29:26.030
and then Father will come out
when you guys are ready.

29:26.031 --> 29:28.133
Wait, hold up.
We're doing this in front of everybody?

29:28.134 --> 29:30.268
Yeah.
That's right.

29:30.269 --> 29:34.304
Great. So just let me know
when you're all set, okay?

29:38.743 --> 29:39.744
Hey, Patrick?

29:39.745 --> 29:40.745
Yeah.

29:40.746 --> 29:41.913
Hey, man, does your
camera shoot video?

29:41.914 --> 29:43.548
Yeah.

29:43.549 --> 29:45.917
Think you could help me get some...
during this?

29:45.918 --> 29:47.552
Definitely.

29:47.553 --> 29:49.553
Where do you want me to shoot from?

29:52.123 --> 29:54.259
I mean, anywhere where you
can get a good shot of Sam

29:54.260 --> 29:58.396
asking some questions and
then you can flip around

29:58.397 --> 30:00.932
and get some shots of
people, that'd be awesome.

30:00.933 --> 30:02.634
All right, maybe I'll
just set up over here.

30:02.635 --> 30:04.267
Yeah.
Thanks, man.

30:08.439 --> 30:11.208
Well, light looks pretty good.

31:00.992 --> 31:02.460
Father's here!

31:55.613 --> 31:57.115
Hi.

31:57.116 --> 31:58.882
Nice to meet you.

32:01.419 --> 32:04.255
Yeah.
All right, all right.

32:04.256 --> 32:06.057
Let me get rigged up here.

32:06.058 --> 32:08.293
All right.
All right.

32:08.294 --> 32:12.797
Well, I trust your stay so
far has been hospitable.

32:12.798 --> 32:16.200
What we lack in modern comfort,
we make up for in humanity.

32:16.201 --> 32:17.201
Isn't that right?

32:22.440 --> 32:23.942
It's been pretty amazing.

32:23.943 --> 32:25.777
Everyone we talked to
seems to feel that

32:25.778 --> 32:27.312
this is everything they ever wanted

32:27.313 --> 32:28.646
and they all credit you for that.

32:28.647 --> 32:30.815
Oh, I don't deserve the credit.

32:30.816 --> 32:32.951
We all did this together.

32:32.952 --> 32:36.087
We built this place
from the ground up.

32:36.088 --> 32:39.324
This is our community and
you being our visitors,

32:39.325 --> 32:41.092
it is just as much yours.

32:41.093 --> 32:42.559
That's what we believe in.

32:44.595 --> 32:45.830
I want to talk more about that,

32:45.831 --> 32:48.466
but I would love to get some
basics out of the way first.

32:48.467 --> 32:51.102
Caroline mentioned you were
little under the whether earlier,

32:51.103 --> 32:52.971
so I hope this is not too much.

32:52.972 --> 32:54.605
Oh, yeah.
I'm fine.

32:54.606 --> 32:55.840
Great.

32:55.841 --> 32:58.810
Okay, so first off.
Can I ask your real name?

32:58.811 --> 33:02.447
Everybody here has been calling you
Father and I wonder how that started.

33:02.448 --> 33:04.381
Well, it's a nickname.

33:05.450 --> 33:08.987
I don't remember exactly when it
started, but it was many years ago.

33:08.988 --> 33:12.957
Some people see anyone who
extends a helping hand

33:12.958 --> 33:14.492
as a father figure.

33:14.493 --> 33:16.961
And yes, that's where it came from.

33:16.962 --> 33:20.765
My given name is
Charles Anderson Reed.

33:20.766 --> 33:22.333
That's a great name.

33:22.334 --> 33:25.870
Where are you from and how
did all of this get started?

33:25.871 --> 33:27.138
Can you take us through it?

33:27.139 --> 33:30.875
Oh, I am from all over, friend.

33:30.876 --> 33:33.778
I've been in every big
city and every small town.

33:33.779 --> 33:36.147
And you know what I found?

33:36.148 --> 33:42.919
Poverty, violence,
greed and racism.

33:44.155 --> 33:47.625
The foundations of a
cancerous society

33:47.626 --> 33:49.160
and I felt it to make a difference.

33:49.161 --> 33:51.896
You see all these
people here tonight?

33:51.897 --> 33:55.666
They all came here because
they had nothing.

33:55.667 --> 33:58.002
They were born outcast.

33:58.003 --> 33:59.871
Never given a chance.

33:59.872 --> 34:02.173
I know, 'cause so was I.

34:02.174 --> 34:08.679
Society turned its back on these
people years ago, but I never will.

34:08.679 --> 34:10.648
I grew up poor.

34:10.649 --> 34:12.417
I know that pain.

34:12.418 --> 34:17.155
I know what it's like to
lose hope, to feel trapped.

34:17.156 --> 34:19.056
Well, there's none of that here.

34:19.058 --> 34:21.426
You come down here and I'll
give you a place to live.

34:21.427 --> 34:24.929
I'll give you a job, I'll give you
some good, I'll give you a bed.

34:24.929 --> 34:26.264
Whatever you need.

34:26.264 --> 34:27.431
That's right!

34:27.433 --> 34:29.900
And we could live
our lives, friend.

34:29.902 --> 34:31.536
Truly live.

34:31.536 --> 34:34.438
There is definitely a
sense of togetherness,

34:34.440 --> 34:38.208
but I do wonder if this isolation
is the only way to achieve that.

34:38.210 --> 34:39.577
Well, I had hoped not,

34:39.578 --> 34:44.047
but I believe for the
time being that's so.

34:44.049 --> 34:48.453
You see, we built this
congregation over many years.

34:48.454 --> 34:52.556
We travel around and preach a
good word, wherever we went.

34:52.558 --> 34:55.460
And every stop we
made we'd pick up one

34:55.460 --> 34:58.096
or two of God's lost children.

34:58.097 --> 35:00.098
You know what we found
more often than not?

35:00.099 --> 35:02.600
It's a struggle to
bring people together.

35:02.601 --> 35:06.370
America is coming
apart at the seams

35:06.371 --> 35:11.709
because of the way it's being
run, and the values it instills.

35:11.710 --> 35:13.611
Your government is failing, friend.

35:13.612 --> 35:16.481
Now before you call me a
communist or socialist

35:16.482 --> 35:18.116
or whatever word you use

35:18.117 --> 35:20.985
for somebody who tries
to help this fellow men,

35:20.986 --> 35:24.322
let me remind you of one thing,

35:24.323 --> 35:27.125
all the great leaders who
have tried to achieve

35:27.126 --> 35:30.995
what we have here were
struck down and killed.

35:30.996 --> 35:32.330
That's right.

35:32.331 --> 35:34.632
Malcolm X.

35:34.633 --> 35:36.767
Martin Luther King.
Oh, my God.

35:36.768 --> 35:39.270
J.F.K.

35:39.271 --> 35:41.272
R.F.K.

35:41.273 --> 35:43.508
Well, I'm willing to die
for what I believe in,

35:43.509 --> 35:51.181
when you can remove yourself from the fight
altogether and create something new.

35:51.916 --> 35:55.019
A place without violence.

35:55.020 --> 35:58.256
Romans Chapter 12 verse 2.

35:58.257 --> 36:02.660
"Do not conform any longer to
the pattern of this world,

36:02.661 --> 36:08.898
but be transformed by the
renewing of your mind."

36:11.002 --> 36:15.071
And that way you can test
and prove God's will.

36:15.873 --> 36:20.511
God's good and pleasing
and perfect will.

36:20.512 --> 36:22.446
That's what we do here, see?

36:22.447 --> 36:26.784
We are continuing our
cause peacefully.

36:26.785 --> 36:28.686
Surely you can appreciate that.

36:28.687 --> 36:30.521
Absolutely.

36:30.522 --> 36:33.691
Speaking to that point,
when we came in,

36:33.692 --> 36:36.060
we noticed there were
a few men with guns.

36:36.061 --> 36:37.895
If this is a pacifist community,

36:37.896 --> 36:42.033
and it seems as if
it is, why the guns?

36:42.034 --> 36:45.168
Is there some paranoia
about the outside world?

36:45.970 --> 36:47.838
Today a woman even
called us outsiders.

36:47.839 --> 36:48.973
Oh.

36:48.974 --> 36:51.676
You see, this is why I
don't like the media.

36:54.680 --> 36:56.314
We have been speaking five minutes

36:56.315 --> 36:59.817
and you're already looking for
some negative angle to explore.

36:59.818 --> 37:03.321
Oh, no, I don't blame you, Sam.
It's not your fault.

37:03.322 --> 37:04.989
You don't even know
you're doing it.

37:04.990 --> 37:07.058
It's just the way you've
been conditioned.

37:07.059 --> 37:10.595
Come in here from a
sick, violent society,

37:10.596 --> 37:13.064
it's only natural that
you'd be less interested

37:13.065 --> 37:17.735
in the beauty of our community than in
the guns we use to protect the borders.

37:17.736 --> 37:18.736
I wasn't saying...

37:18.737 --> 37:21.739
What we're doing here is radical,
Sam, there's no doubt about it.

37:21.740 --> 37:26.010
And it is complicated, that's why
I want to explain it to you.

37:26.011 --> 37:28.246
I have sympathy for
your misunderstanding.

37:28.247 --> 37:29.747
We all do.

37:29.748 --> 37:31.714
We all used to think just like you.

37:32.883 --> 37:36.887
Let me just say that there are
certain government agencies

37:36.888 --> 37:41.024
that have been watching me and
my congregation for many years,

37:41.892 --> 37:43.394
everybody knows that.

37:43.395 --> 37:45.763
I do not keep it secret.

37:45.764 --> 37:48.099
But I made a promise
to these people

37:48.100 --> 37:52.136
that I would lead them
to a better existence

37:52.137 --> 37:54.237
and that includes protecting them.

37:56.274 --> 37:59.043
It's our home down here,
we have to preserve it.

37:59.044 --> 38:00.411
That's understandable.

38:00.412 --> 38:03.146
Yeah, see?
I knew he'd catch on.

38:03.981 --> 38:08.786
Living in that beehive New York
City has jaded you completely.

38:08.787 --> 38:10.154
That's good.

38:10.155 --> 38:12.188
So...

38:13.291 --> 38:16.794
It must have cost quite a bit
of money to create all this.

38:16.795 --> 38:20.298
Was it just through donations all
these people's life savings?

38:20.299 --> 38:21.932
Oh, Sam.

38:21.933 --> 38:25.569
I hate you, you
phrase it like that.

38:25.570 --> 38:28.139
Is that what money means to you?

38:28.140 --> 38:29.273
A life?

38:29.274 --> 38:32.443
We don't worship capitalism
and materialism.

38:32.444 --> 38:35.179
We came down here to
live off the land.

38:35.180 --> 38:38.916
That's why America started,
but they don't allow it anymore.

38:38.917 --> 38:41.452
Yeah, if you're not paying
taxes then you go to jail.

38:41.453 --> 38:43.788
Exactly.
That is exactly right.

38:43.789 --> 38:46.856
Now, Sam, let me ask you
a question if I may.

38:47.925 --> 38:50.961
Look around here,
look at all these people.

38:50.962 --> 38:55.965
Do you see anybody who looks
like they ought to go to jail?

39:00.037 --> 39:01.471
It doesn't look like it, no.

39:02.606 --> 39:05.209
That's right.

39:05.210 --> 39:07.044
I see you wear a
ring on your finger.

39:07.045 --> 39:09.680
You are married man, are you?

39:09.681 --> 39:10.715
Yes.

39:10.716 --> 39:11.982
Oh, that's good.

39:11.983 --> 39:13.883
You love your wife?

39:14.985 --> 39:16.120
Excuse me?

39:16.121 --> 39:19.222
A simple question.
Do you love your wife?

39:20.191 --> 39:21.859
Yes, of course.

39:21.860 --> 39:23.961
And you'd do anything for her.

39:23.962 --> 39:28.264
And what about that child
you have on the way?

39:29.700 --> 39:31.235
Oh, what's wrong?

39:31.236 --> 39:34.872
You seem caught off
guard by my question.

39:34.873 --> 39:37.840
Interesting when the shoe is
on the other foot, isn't it?

39:39.977 --> 39:43.481
And I suppose you were wondering how I
knew that about your wife, aren't you?

39:43.482 --> 39:46.217
Oh, relax, Sam.
I'm just making a point here.

39:46.218 --> 39:49.220
You see, I love these people here

39:49.221 --> 39:53.491
just as much as you love your
wife and your unborn child.

39:53.492 --> 39:58.329
These people,
my family, my children.

39:58.330 --> 40:00.431
And when you write this
up for your readers,

40:00.432 --> 40:04.001
I want you to remember that.

40:04.002 --> 40:07.505
And when you start to
put that spin on it,

40:07.506 --> 40:11.375
just know that you're
dealing with their lives,

40:11.376 --> 40:15.212
with those faces.

40:15.213 --> 40:18.949
Look at the joy on those faces.

40:18.950 --> 40:21.985
Remember what you're
seeing tonight, Sam.

40:24.021 --> 40:26.223
You have a great responsibility.

40:26.224 --> 40:28.157
I hope you're aware.

40:31.028 --> 40:32.897
I am.

40:32.898 --> 40:35.032
But we don't spin things.

40:35.033 --> 40:36.867
We try to be honestly subjective.

40:36.868 --> 40:38.602
We don't have an agenda,

40:38.603 --> 40:40.905
we're just trying to document
things that are meaningful.

40:40.906 --> 40:44.742
Oh, yeah, that's right.
Caroline told me that.

40:44.743 --> 40:47.411
That's why I agreed
to this interview.

40:47.412 --> 40:50.381
You know, I don't
believe in the media.

40:50.382 --> 40:55.419
I see it always lies
upon lies upon lies.

40:55.420 --> 40:58.187
Anything that'll sell more copies.

41:00.791 --> 41:04.060
But I look at you, Sam, and I
can tell you're different.

41:05.763 --> 41:07.830
I can see that you care.

41:10.167 --> 41:11.802
We try.

41:11.803 --> 41:14.537
Yes, you do.

41:17.641 --> 41:19.443
Well, are there anymore questions

41:19.444 --> 41:23.781
or can we quit all this and get on
to the celebration we got planned?

41:23.782 --> 41:25.182
We got a wonderful band.

41:25.183 --> 41:26.450
I know you're gonna love him.

41:32.857 --> 41:33.958
I guess we're fine.

41:33.959 --> 41:35.025
All right.

42:22.740 --> 42:28.644
Yo, so that was one of the strangest
interviews I've ever done.

42:29.880 --> 42:31.882
Shit. man.

42:31.883 --> 42:35.886
Yeah, if you could see, I only...

42:35.887 --> 42:37.988
Yeah, I only got through
about a quarter

42:37.989 --> 42:40.658
of my questions and
really I'm not sure

42:40.659 --> 42:43.727
if any of those even got answered.

42:43.728 --> 42:45.029
Everything just sort
of got swept up

42:45.030 --> 42:50.267
in this weird energy and I
couldn't think straight.

42:50.268 --> 42:53.270
He had a way about him.

42:53.271 --> 42:55.906
That's hard to focus.

42:55.907 --> 42:58.909
Well, the thing about my
wife really stunned me.

42:58.910 --> 43:01.545
And you were saying that
he must have heard it

43:01.546 --> 43:03.914
